<subSubSection pageId="32" pageNumber="131" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="32.[144,759,259,679]" pageId="32" pageNumber="131">
<emphasis box="[144,402,259,280]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="131">Differential diagnosis:</emphasis>
Very distinct species with a medial black facial vitta, cell BM bare on basal half, and abdominal terga 3 and 4 each with a narrow yellow fascia (
<figureCitation box="[305,433,351,373]" captionStart="Figures 15–26" captionStartId="14.[144,234,1643,1662]" captionTargetBox="[281,1292,195,1601]" captionTargetId="figure-0@14.[271,1295,195,1613]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="Figures 15–26. Dorsal view of abdomen. 15–16, Citrogramma bicornutum: 15, female; 16, male. 17, Citrogramma asombrosum, male. 18–19, Citrogramma quadratum: 18, male; 19, female. 20–21, Citrogramma arisanicum: 20, male; 21, female. 22, Citrogramma australe, male. 23–24, Citrogramma notiale: 22, female; 24, male. 25–26, Citrogramma robertsi: 25, female; 26, male." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5406161" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5406161/files/figure.png" pageId="32" pageNumber="131">Figs 15, 16</figureCitation>
). Similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mengual" authorityYear="2012" box="[576,752,351,373]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Citrogramma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="asombrosum">
<emphasis box="[576,752,351,373]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="131">C. asombrosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but they differ in male genitalia, abdominal pattern (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mengual" authorityYear="2012" box="[152,327,412,434]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Citrogramma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="asombrosum">
<emphasis box="[152,327,412,434]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="131">C. asombrosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a broad yellow fascia on terga 3 and 4) and geographical distribution (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mengual" authorityYear="2012" box="[583,758,443,464]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Citrogramma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="131" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="asombrosum">
<emphasis box="[583,758,443,464]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="131">C. asombrosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is only known from 
<collectingCountry box="[380,559,474,496]" name="New Caledonia" pageId="32" pageNumber="131">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
).
</paragraph>
